                <head>No. 495.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of the United States</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">President of Mexico</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-03-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 5, 1881</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President of the United States sends to the President of the Republic of
                    Mexico the cordial congratulations of the government and <pb facs="0950" n="826"
                        xml:id="pg_826"/> people of this country upon the successful completion, by
                    submarine cable, of connections between the telegraph systems of the two
                    countries.</p>
                <p>It must be a great satisfaction to your distinguished predecessor as well as
                    yourself to see so beneficent a fruit from the wise policy of your successive
                    administration.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
